Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Remove @Cheese Pizza{1} and @Pepperoni Pizza{1} from box and plastic wrapping.

Place pizzas on a #baking sheet{} (depending on the size of your sheet, you may need to use two). Bake on middle rack until @mozzarella{} melts and crusts are golden brown, ~{12-14%minutes} if frozen or ~{10-12%minutes} if thawed.

Remove baking sheet from oven and let pizzas cool for ~{2%minutes} before serving.

> When it comes to pizza, these classic pies made with light and fluffy focaccia are just as tasty as they are easy. Both pies are made with premium mozzarella and tomato sauce; one is plain cheese and the other is topped with pepperoni. The best part? They're ready in less than 20 minutes. So, let Dad take a load off for pizza night—it's the yeast you can do!